            <pb facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                <hi rendition="#b">A Day of Distress from Alexander Hum-<lb/>boldt.</hi></head>
                <lb/>
                <p>Berlin papers reserved by the City of Balti-<lb/>
                    more contain the following card from Alexander<lb/>
                Humboldt:</p>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#right"><hi rendition="#k">Berlin,</hi> March 15, &#x2019;59.</hi>
                </dateline>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>Suffering beneath the pressure of a still in-<lb/>
                    creasing correspondence, amounting to between<lb/>
                    sixteen hundred and two thousand communica-<lb/>
                    tions per annum, and embracing letters, printed<lb/>
                    pamphlets on matters with which I am wholly<lb/>
                    unacquainted, manuscripts concerning which my<lb/>
                    opinion is desired, projects for emigration and<lb/>
                    colonizing, the sending of models, machines and<lb/>
                    natural curiosities, requests of contributions to<lb/>
                    collections of autographs, offers to take charge<lb/>
                    of my domestic concerns, to cheer and enliven<lb/>
                    me, &amp;c., &amp;c., I must again publicly urge all<lb/>
                    persons having my welfare at heart to exert<lb/>
                    their influence in my behalf, that individuals in<lb/>
                    both continents may no longer busy themselves<lb/>
                    with my person, and make of my house an in-<lb/>
                    telligence office; and that I be allowed, in the<lb/>
                    declining state of my physical and mental pow-<lb/>
                    ers, to enjoy some rest and leisure to attend to<lb/>
                    my duties. May this cry for relief, which I ut-<lb/>
                    ter with much reluctance and after reflection,<lb/>
                    not meet an unfriendly interpretation!</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#right"><hi rendition="#k">Alexander Von Humboldt.</hi></hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb/>
            <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/>
            <lb/>
        </body>
